        <Desc>THE ADULT MAINTENANCE PROGRAM (AMP) IS A SPECIALIZED STRUCTURED PROGRAM FOR BOTH MEN AND WOMEN. THE PURPOSE OF THE AMP IS TO PROVIDE SAFE TRANSITIONAL HOUSING FOR INDIVIDUALS WHO NEED ADDITIONAL ACCOUNTABILITY AND STRUCTURE, BUT DO NOT MEET REQUIREMENTS FOR RESIDENTIAL CARE. THE AMP PROGRAM IS OFFERED AS ALTERNATIVE TO THE HIGH COST OF INPATIENT TREATMENT. THE GOAL OF THE AMP PROGRAM IS TO SUPPORT PARTICIPANTS AS THEY ACQUIRE GAINFUL EMPLOYMENT AND SEEK PERMANENT HOUSING.</Desc>
      </ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp>
